text.__SUMMARY__: Odostomia nova is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Description: The shell grows to a length of 3 mm.
text.Distribution: This species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off Argentina.
